Problema 3

1.11-1 Provide MATLAB code and output that plots the odd portion (t) of the function over a suitable-length interval using a suitable number of points.
u1 = @(t1) 1.0.*(t1>=0);
f = @(t1) (2.^-t1).*cos(2*pi*t1);
t1 = (0:0.01:10);
S = f(t1).*u1(t1-pi);
subplot(3,1,1),plot(t1,S,'color','r'),title('x(t) Original');
xlabel('t'); ylabel('x(t)');
grid on; hold on;
R = (f(t1).*u1(t1-pi)-(f(-t1).*u1(-t1-pi)))/2;
subplot(3,1,2),plot(t1,R,'color','b'),title('x(t) impar');
xlabel('t'); ylabel('-x(-t)');
grid on;
subplot(3,1,3),plot(t1,R), title('Original vs impar');
hold on;
subplot(3,1,3),plot(t1,S);
legend('impar','Original');
set(gcf,'color','y');
xlabel('t'); ylabel('-x(-t)');
grid on; hold off;
